de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler

Class TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2_IDS_SL900A

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_Base
      • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2
        • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2_IDS_SL900A

  • public class TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2_IDS_SL900A
extends TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2
    Class for HF/UHF transponder EPC Class 1 Generation 2 of manufacturer IDS Microchip .
    This class supports only addressed or non-addressed mode in Host-Mode
    .
    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.
    All methods are similiar to the specific commands of the IDS SL900A. Thus, you must refer to the Technical Datasheet of the SL900A to get detailed information about the methods and the parameters.
    Secondly, all methods of this class are Custom specific commands, realized with the Reader command [0xB4], which are described in the Application Note IDS Custom and Proprietary Commands_UHF.pdf

        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes

      • accessFIFO

        public int accessFIFO(java.lang.String accessPassword,
                      byte subCommand,
                      byte[] payload)
               throws FeException
        [0xB4][0xAF] Access FIFO : can read and write data from the FIFO and can also read the FIFO status register.
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Refer to the Application Note IDS Custom and Proprietary Commands_UHF.pdf, where all parameters are described in detail.
        If transmission was successful and subCommand = SUB_CMD_READ_FIFO or SUB_CMD_READ_STATUS, the data were written into the member attributes:
        m_payload or m_fifoStatusRegister.
